<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>48-831.22</num>
  <heading>Eligibility for low-income elderly.</heading>
  <text>To be eligible, an individual shall:</text>
  <para>
    <num>(1)</num>
    <text>Be a resident of the District;</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(2)</num>
    <text>Be at least 62 years of age; and</text>
  </para>
  <para>
    <num>(3)</num>
    <text>Have a household income that is not more than 200% of the federal poverty level.</text>
  </para>
  <annotations>
